reviews.review_text: Aud as OK to not so good...but this is a great listen This show is a great one.  A good deal of imagination and no-one is in a rush.  The Estimated into Franklins has imagination.  The Franklins intro is lengthy and the jam out if Franklins into drums is a pleasure.

bread crumb Think that second set looks unusual?  You're right, this is the only time that Eyes, Estimated, Lost Sailor > St. of Circumstance and Franklin's were all played together in a set, regardless of order or pairings.  I've commented previously on Eyes > Estimated, which is rare but not singular.  The second set Althea is also pretty rare - 11 times not counting the acoustic set shows - and Franklin's all by it's lonesome is also uncommon.

Flashback?      Having been at that concert, one of the last times I had imbibed a certain substance, it is a great reminder of times past.  It is hard to imagine how any recording could to justice to the intensity, of the segue into "Drums", the Spectrum was a concrete building and it felt like a balsa wood hut.
